1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
In this lesson, we will explore how to set up a privacy policy page.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
It is recommended to all website owners to add a privacy policy page to your site,

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
as it is a document required by law that discloses the information you collect about visitors to your website.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
As an example, let's visit WordPress.org and see what their privacy policy page looks like.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
This privacy policy describes how WordPress.org uses and protects information that is given to them.

6
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:35,000
Next, let's discuss how WordPress has made life easier for users.

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
When we open up Pages, you will have noticed that WordPress has simplified the process

8
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
by providing us with a template privacy policy that you can modify to meet your needs.

9
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
There are various subheadings with suggested text,

10
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
but you can add and remove whatever you need.

11
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
And some of the topics that are covered include Media, Cookies,

12
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Embedded content from other websites, Who we share your data with,

13
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
How long we retain your data, What rights you have over your data, and lastly, Where we send your data.

14
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,000
When you are happy with your changes, click Publish.

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Next, we can focus our attention on privacy settings.

16
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Let's make our way to the dashboard, scroll down to Settings and click on Privacy.

17
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
You will be able to edit or preview your privacy policy page

18
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
and check out the Privacy Policy Guide for extra help and support.

19
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
When you scroll down, you have the option to create a new privacy policy

20
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
and change or assign the privacy policy page you are using.

21
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
In the last section, I am going to add my privacy policy page to my footer.

22
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
So, I am going to make my way to Appearance and then click on Editor.

23
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
And this will of course take me into the Site Editor where I can edit my header and footer.

24
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
I can of course edit my header and footer within the template.

25
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
But to edit my footer with less distractions, I am going to make my way to Navigation

26
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:14,000
and select the footer navigation.

27
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,000
I will open up the Template Editing Mode and then click on the Inserter of the Navigation block

28
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:24,000
and add my privacy page.

29
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
Once added, I can click Save.

30
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,000
And when I return to my Home Template and scroll down,

31
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
I will see that my privacy policy page is now part of my footer below Quick Links.

32
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
It is also worth mentioning that you can generate a privacy policy using a plugin.

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
All the best as you set up your privacy statement.

